content: Strait south of Singapore The **Pandan Strait** is a [strait](/wiki/Strait) south of [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore)'s [main island](/wiki/Pulau_Ujong). It separates the [man-made](/wiki/Artificial_island) [Jurong Island](/wiki/Jurong_Island) from the [Southern Islands](/wiki/Southern_Islands). It has a depth of approximately 15 m (49 ft). The strait was partially affected by the *Natuna Sea* [oil spill](/wiki/Oil_spill) in October 2000. - [Singapore Strait](/wiki/Singapore_Strait) 1°14′58″N 103°43′45″E﻿ / ﻿1.24944°N 103.72917°E﻿ / 1.24944; 103.72917 This [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) location article is a stub.
